This course introduces different qualitative research and data analysis methods used in economics and social sciences. An overview of basic principles of carrying out interviews, surveys, observations, case studies etc. will be given. Relationships between research object, research problems and aims, theoretical standpoints and research methods are introduced. Topics of research planning, data collection, data analysis and presenting of results in qualitative research will be covered. Course ends with an introduction of different quantitative and qualitative data analysis methods.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course enables to get knowledge of different methods used in data gathering and analysis in qualitative and quantitative research in economics and social sciences and the main principles and problems of research methodology. Enables to develop students' analytical skills, critical thinking and is meant for improving the level of students' master projects.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course, the student: *is able to reflect over the role of research in nowadays society  * knows the main methodologies and methods, used in social sciences on  *is able to formulate a research problem for his/her master thesis  *is able to create an introduction to his/her master thesis (research problem, research aim and research tasks) together with a logical structure of the thesis - the table of contents  *knows how to conduct qualitative data analysis  *knows how to conduct quantitative data analysis  *has acquired the skills of writing a master thesis,
